    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="99" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Burnley</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 28, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the note which you did
                            me the honor to address to me on the 15th December last, relative to
                            shot fired from a battery at Eastport, having fallen on British
                            territory, I am directed by her Majesty’s government to state to you
                            that they have received with satisfaction the assurance contained in
                            your above-mentioned note, that instructions will be given to prevent
                            any further shots being fired from the battery at Eastport into British
                            territory, and that the occurrence in question was unauthorized,
                            inadvertent, and was to be regretted.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most
                            obedient, humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. HUME BURNLEY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
